  29,38,"And the people of ‚Äô»ād and Tham√Ľd ňĻmet a similar fateňļ, which must be clear to you ňĻMeccansňļ from their ruins.¬†Satan made their ňĻevilňļ deeds appealing to them, hindering them from the ňĻRightňļ Way, although they were capable of reasoning"
  29,39,"ňĻWeňļ also ňĻdestroyedňļ Korah, Pharaoh, and Ham√Ęn. Indeed, Moses had come to them with clear proofs, but they behaved arrogantly in the land. Yet they could not escape ňĻUsňļ"
  29,40,"So We seized each ňĻpeopleňļ for their sin: against some of them We sent a storm of stones, some were overtaken by a ňĻmightyňļ blast, some We caused the earth to swallow, and some We drowned. Allah would not have wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  29,41,"The parable of those who take protectors other than Allah is that of a spider spinning a shelter. And the flimsiest of all shelters is certainly that of a spider, if only they knew"
  29,42,"Allah surely knows that whatever ňĻgodsňļ they invoke besides Him are ňĻsimplyňļ nothing. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  29,43,"These are the parables We set forth for humanity, but none will understand them except the people of knowledge"
  29,44,Allah created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. Surely in this is a sign for the people of faith
  29,45,"Recite what has been revealed to you of the Book and establish prayer. Indeed, ňĻgenuineňļ prayer should deter ňĻoneňļ from indecency and wickedness. The remembrance of Allah is ňĻanňļ even greater ňĻdeterrentňļ. And Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows what you ňĻallňļ do"